                    <h2 class="article-title">Reducing Water Scarcity by Reducing Food Loss and Waste</h2>
                    <p class="article-summary">Water scarcity is a pervasive threat to society that is expected to intensify alongside a growing and more affluent population and a changing climate. In this paper, we review the existing literature to assess the potential of lessening water scarcity by reducing food loss and waste. Existing studies reveal the scope of food loss and waste and its accompanying impact on water resources, thereby providing a foundation for policy action.</p>
